  "response": "This depends on the context and intentions. Some key considerations:\n\n1. If it's a platonic friendship:\n- Totally fine if boundaries are clear\n- Both people understand it's just friendship\n- No hidden romantic expectations\n\n2. Potential risks:\n- One person might develop romantic feelings\n- It could cause misunderstandings\n- Risk of emotional attachment without commitment\n- Could complicate future relationships\n\n3. Healthy guidelines:\n- Be transparent about intentions\n- Maintain appropriate boundaries\n- Have a clear understanding with the other person\n- Avoid overly intimate conversations\n- Keep communication balanced and respectful\n\n4. Important warning signs:\n- If conversations become flirtatious\n- If one person seems emotionally invested\n- If it's interfering with other relationships\n- If it feels secretive\n\n5. Personal safety:\n- Be cautious about sharing personal information\n- Meet in public if transitioning to in-person interactions\n- Trust your instincts\n\nThe appropriateness depends on individual circumstances, mutual understanding, and maintaining healthy boundaries.",
